<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFC26A7DFD2797381CD8B869" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC26A7DFD2797381CD8B869" blockId="57.[730,1320,275,701]" lastBlockId="57.[113,1321,708,2359]" pageId="57" pageNumber="815">
Placement within 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFC0B97381A66BAB0" box="[1015,1126,353,386]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
is tentative, and the species may be best situated in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFD2797ED1D69BAE3" box="[731,873,436,465]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
, based on genetic data; here retained in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFC6D97811A00BACB" box="[913,1024,472,505]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
, pending more detailed genetic and morphological studies that include more species of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFB86947E1AE9B97A" box="[1146,1257,551,584]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFD2094171D6AB95D" box="[732,874,590,623]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
. Populations of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFC26A7DFB7E94171B28B95D" box="[1154,1320,590,623]" name="Madagascar" pageId="57" pageNumber="815">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
formerly attributed to this species have recently been described as a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFF88949D1F11B9D7" box="[116,273,708,741]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bemainty">H. bemainty</taxonomicName>
, H. anchieta appears to be sister to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFCFE949D1D9EB9D7" box="[770,926,708,741]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bemainty">H. bemainty</taxonomicName>
based on genetic data. The species may be more widely distributed, and some specimens currently attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFF8F954A1F8BB806" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[115,395,787,820]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">Pipistrellus hesperidus</taxonomicName>
may really refer to H. anchieta. The specific epithet is sometimes misspelled 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC26A7DFEEE95631F88B869" baseAuthorityName="Seabra" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[274,392,826,859]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="815" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anchietae">anchietae</taxonomicName>
or anchietai. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
